#. Tag: title
#: examples.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "&step; examples"
msgstr "&step; primeri"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:4
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&step; package contains several instructive examples to help you understand "
"the principles of the application work:"
msgstr ""
"&step; paket vsebuje več poučnih primerov, ki vam bodo pomagali razumeti "
"načela delovanja aplikacije:"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: examples.docbook:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>File</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Examples</guisubmenu>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Primeri</guisubmenu>"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:12
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Opens a submenu</action> with different action items."
msgstr "<action>Odpre podmeni</action> z različnimi elementi dejanj."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: examples.docbook:15
#, no-c-format
msgid "Open Example..."
msgstr "Odpri primer..."

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:16
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Opens an example</action> from the default set"
msgstr "<action>Odpre primer</action> iz privzetega nabora"

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: examples.docbook:19
#, no-c-format
msgid "Open Downloaded Example..."
msgstr "Odpri preneseni primer..."

#. Tag: action
#: examples.docbook:20
#, no-c-format
msgid "Opens the downloaded examples."
msgstr "Odpre prenesene primere."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: examples.docbook:23
#, no-c-format
msgid "Download New Experiments..."
msgstr "Prenesite nove poskuse..."

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Download examples</action> shared by other users."
msgstr "<action>Prenesi primere</action>, ki so jih delili drugi uporabniki."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: examples.docbook:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "Share Current Experiment..."
msgstr "Deli trenutni poskus..."

#. Tag: action
#: examples.docbook:28
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can share your own examples."
msgstr "Lahko delite svoje primere."

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:35
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can find the descriptions of the default example files below."
msgstr "Spodaj najdete opise privzetih primerov datotek."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:40
#, no-c-format
msgid "brownian.step"
msgstr "brownian.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:41
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Plots trajectory of the rigid disk interacting with 40 particles that "
"randomly drifting in a box. This example simulates <ulink url=\"https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/Brownian_motion\">Brownian motion</ulink> of ideal gas "
"particles."
msgstr ""
"Nariše trajektorijo togega diska v interakciji s 40 delci, ki naključno "
"lebdijo v škatli. Ta primer simulira <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/"
"wiki/Brownian_motion\">Brownovo gibanje</ulink> delcev idealnega plina."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:45
#, no-c-format
msgid "doublependulum.step"
msgstr "doublependulum.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:46
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This example simulates <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Double_pendulum\">double pendulum motion</ulink> using 2 massive particles "
"and two sticks."
msgstr ""
"Ta primer simulira <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Double_pendulum"
"\">gibanje dvojnega nihala</ulink> z uporabo dveh masivnih delcev in dveh "
"palic."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:50
#, no-c-format
msgid "eightpendulum.step"
msgstr "eightpendulum.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This example is a simple demonstration of the famous <ulink url=\"https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/Newton%27s_cradle\">Newton's cradle</ulink>. It is done "
"in &step; using sticks, 8 discs and a box. The six balls in the middle are "
"not moving because they just transfer momentum and energy, not a motion."
msgstr ""
"Ta primer je preprosta predstavitev slavne <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/Newton%27s_cradle\">Newtonove zibelke</ulink>. Izvede se v &step; z "
"uporabo palic, 8 diskov in škatle. Šest kroglic na sredini se ne premika, "
"ker le prenašajo zagon in energijo, ne pa gibanja."

#. Tag: term
#: examples.docbook:55
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>first.step</filename>: First example"
msgstr "<filename>first.step</filename>: Prvi primer"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:56
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This example has two parts. The first part contains two particles connected "
"by a spring and the second part contains two charged particles."
msgstr ""
"Ta primer ima dva dela. Prvi del vsebuje dva delca, povezana z vzmetjo, "
"drugi del pa dva nabita delca."

#. Tag: term
#: examples.docbook:60
#, no-c-format
msgid "Two particles connected by a spring"
msgstr "Dva delca, povezana z vzmetjo"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:61
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this example two particles are added to the scene and spring is connected "
"between them. The properties of both the particles such as velocity, "
"momentum, position &etc; has been set in the properties browser. The "
"properties of the spring such as stiffness, restLength, damping &etc; also "
"has been set in the properties browser."
msgstr ""
"V tem primeru sta na sceno dodana dva delca in med njima je povezana vzmet. "
"Lastnosti obeh delcev, kot so hitrost, zagon, položaj &etc; je nastavljen v "
"brskalniku lastnosti. Lastnosti vzmeti, kot so togost, dolžina mirovanja, "
"dušenje &etc; nastavljen tudi v brskalniku lastnosti."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: examples.docbook:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "Explanation of the simulation:"
msgstr "Razlaga simulacije:"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is good example of a simple harmonic motion. Here the acceleration of "
"the one particle is set in direction of positive x-axis and the acceleration "
"of the other particle is set along negative x-axis. As a result both the "
"particles pulls the spring in opposite directions, where as spring tries to "
"bring the two particles back to their original positions. Thus the system "
"executes simple harmonic motion. The simulation of the particles and spring "
"under these conditions can be seen on the scene."
msgstr ""
"To je dober primer preprostega harmoničnega gibanja. Tukaj je pospešek enega "
"delca nastavljen v smeri pozitivne osi x, pospešek drugega delca pa vzdolž "
"negativne osi x. Posledica tega je, da oba delca vlečeta vzmet v nasprotni "
"smeri, kjer vzmet skuša oba delca vrniti v prvotni položaj. Tako sistem "
"izvaja preprosto harmonično gibanje. Simulacija delcev in vzmeti pod temi "
"pogoji je vidna na prizorišču."

#. Tag: term
#: examples.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "Two charged particles"
msgstr "Dva nabita delca"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Velocity of the each charged particle is set in some direction so, the "
"charged particles moves in respective direction of their velocity but each "
"particle has been given a equal and opposite charge so the particles try to "
"attract each other. As a result the simulation of the charged particles "
"under these conditions can be seen on the scene."
msgstr ""
"Hitrost vsakega nabitega delca je nastavljena v določeni smeri, tako da se "
"nabiti delci gibljejo v ustrezni smeri svoje hitrosti, vendar je vsakemu "
"delcu dodeljen enak in nasproten naboj, tako da se delci poskušajo "
"pritegniti. Posledično je na prizorišču mogoče videti simulacijo nabitih "
"delcev pod temi pogoji."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "fourpendula.step"
msgstr "fourpendula.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This example is a correct demonstration of the <ulink url=\"https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/Newton%27s_cradle\">Newton's cradle</ulink>. As the "
"system is imperfect two disks in the middle get visual movement with time."
msgstr ""
"Ta primer je pravilna predstavitev <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/"
"wiki/Newton%27s_cradle\">Newtonove zibelke</ulink>. Ker je sistem nepopoln, "
"se dva diska na sredini s časom vizualno premikata."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:85
#, no-c-format
msgid "gas.step"
msgstr "gas.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:86
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This example simulates ideal gas pressure caused by <ulink url=\"https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/Brownian_motion\">Brownian motion</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Ta primer simulira idealni plinski tlak, ki ga povzroča <ulink url=\"https://"
"en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brownian_motion\">Brownovo gibanje</ulink>."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:90
#, no-c-format
msgid "graph.step"
msgstr "graph.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Plots velocity vs. position graph for particle1 in the system of two "
"particles connected with a spring."
msgstr ""
"Izriše graf hitrosti v odvisnosti od položaja za particle1 v sistemu dveh "
"delcev, povezanih z vzmetjo."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:95
#, no-c-format
msgid "liquid.step"
msgstr "liquid.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:96
#, no-c-format
msgid "This example simulates monoatomic liquid."
msgstr "Ta primer simulira monoatomsko tekočino."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:100
#, no-c-format
msgid "lissajous.step"
msgstr "lissajous.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This example simulates <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Lissajous_curve\">Lissajous curve</ulink> using two-particle model. The "
"parameters on the model can be changed using the controller at the center of "
"the world."
msgstr ""
"Ta primer simulira <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lissajous_curve"
"\">Lissajousovo krivuljo</ulink> z uporabo modela dveh delcev. Parametre na "
"modelu je mogoče spreminjati s pomočjo krmilnika v središču sveta."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:105
#, no-c-format
msgid "motor1.step"
msgstr "motor1.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:106
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Simulates triangular rigid body under the loading of the three linear motors."
msgstr "Simulira trikotno togo telo pod obremenitvijo treh linearnih motorjev."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "motor.step"
msgstr "motor.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Simulates interaction of the linear motor with a rigid rectangular body on a "
"spring."
msgstr ""
"Simulira interakcijo linearnega motorja s togim pravokotnim telesom na "
"vzmeti."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:115
#, no-c-format
msgid "note.step"
msgstr "note.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Example with &latex; formula (<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Divergence_theorem\">divergence theorem</ulink>) and embedded image."
msgstr ""
"Primer z &latex; formula (<ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Divergence_theorem\">divergenčni izrek</ulink>) in vdelana slika."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid "resonance.step"
msgstr "resonance.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:121
#, no-c-format
msgid "This example simulates resonance in the system with angular motor."
msgstr "Ta primer simulira resonanco v sistemu s kotnim motorjem."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:125
#, no-c-format
msgid "softbody.step"
msgstr "softbody.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This example simulates interaction of two rigid bodies with a soft body "
"between them."
msgstr ""
"Ta primer simulira interakcijo dveh togih teles z mehkim telesom med njima."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid "solar.step"
msgstr "solar.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This example simulates the motion of Solar system major bodies (Sun and the "
"planets)."
msgstr "Ta primer simulira gibanje glavnih teles Osončja (Sonce in planeti)."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:135
#, no-c-format
msgid "springs.step"
msgstr "springs.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:136
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This example simulates the motion of the planar system of five particles "
"connected with four springs."
msgstr ""
"Ta primer simulira gibanje ravninskega sistema petih delcev, povezanih s "
"štirimi vzmetmi."

#. Tag: filename
#: examples.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid "wave.step"
msgstr "wave.step"

#. Tag: para
#: examples.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The graph on the scene shows oscillations of the green particle. When you "
"start simulation the wave starts to travel from the red particle. The blue "
"particle will reflect the wave and it will travel in reverse direction until "
"the red particle reflects in again. After some time the wave will vanish "
"because springs have damping."
msgstr ""
"Graf na sceni prikazuje nihanje zelenega delca. Ko začnete s simulacijo, val "
"začne potovati od rdečega delca. Modri delec bo odbijal val in potoval v "
"obratni smeri, dokler se rdeči delec ponovno ne odbije. Čez nekaj časa bo "
"val izginil, ker imajo vzmeti dušenje."
